# Product roadmap (source of truth)

The tactical backlog lives in **`docs/ROADMAP.md`**, not in the high-level bullets in `AGENTS.md`.

## Before substantive work

1. Read `docs/ROADMAP.md` (status tables + **Suggested fix order**).
2. Unless the user gives a different priority, work the **next Open item** in **Suggested fix order** (`docs/ROADMAP.md`).
3. If the user’s request maps to a roadmap `#`, treat that item as in scope for the session.

## While working

- Keep changes aligned with the active roadmap item; avoid drive-by refactors.
- If you discover a new bug or requirement, add a row to `docs/ROADMAP.md` (next `#`) and note it in your reply.

## After shipping (same session)

Update `docs/ROADMAP.md` for every item you completed or materially advanced:

| Change | Action |
|--------|--------|
| Shipped | Set **Status** to **Done**; add a short note (commit/PR or file) if helpful |
| Partial | Leave **Open**; add a one-line note under **Known context** or the row |
| Blocked | Leave **Open**; document blocker under **Known context** |
| Deprioritized | Set **Longer-term** or move to a “Deferred” note |

Do not mark **Done** without landing the behavior in the repo.

## Until complete

- Continue roadmap items across sessions until all non–longer-term rows are **Done**, or the user explicitly changes priority.
- Item **#18** (spec-driven tasks) is **Done** for v1–v5; follow [RELEASE.md](../docs/RELEASE.md) for submodule tagging. Deeper Kiro parity is longer-term only.

